egration: merge logic). A pure Integration test with mocks won't catch concurrency bugs or how the system behaves under real model latency. A System or Agentic test alone misses either the parallelism aspects or the AI quality aspects. Only Workflow-level testing—real AI calls running in parallel on real contracts with full orchestration—can reveal whether the pipeline completes correctly without losing findings.","test_description":"Execute the full pipeline on a real or realistic contract: dispatch to all three reviewers in parallel (real AI calls), collect results from all three, merge into a unified report. Run multiple times and verify: (1) all three reviewers are invoked, (2) no findings are lost during collection or merge, (3) the pipeline completes even if one reviewer is slow (timeout handling), (4) concurrent execution doesn't cause data races. Failure mode: race condition causes one reviewer's output to be overwritten, timeout on one reviewer drops its findings, or merge silently discards assessments under concurrent load.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13368,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13368},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3a229f2b-082b-48c5-a8b6-5a80bd731b7a","uuid":"e1cd23d4-e8af-4bca-9243-d991fc15b256"}
